           <h3 class='wedding-cake'>
              <h1><p><u>Wedding Cake</u></p></h1> 
          <p>A wedding cake are made to bring good luck to all the guest and the couples.
            In some parts of England, the wedding cake is served as breakfast; 
            <em>Breakfast</em> does not mean the meal will be in the morning 
            but at a time following the ceremony. A wedding cake is the traditional cake served at wedding receptions following dinner. 
            Nowadays, however they are more of a centerpiece to the wedding and are not always even served to the guests. 
            some cakes are built with single edible tiers for the bride and groom to share.
             we have different types of wedding cakes; <li>Red Velvet Cake.</li> <li>chocolate Cake.</li> <li>Carrot Cake.</li> <li>Vanilla Cake.</li>
             <li>Spice Cake.</li> <li>Caramel Banana Cake.</li> <li>Many More.</li>
             <h4>Subscribe to our Blog, so you can see different recipes for this different types of cake when we post them.</h4>
          </p>

          <h1><u>Pastries</u></p></h1>
          <p>Pastries  is a dough of flour, water and solids fats that may be  savoury or sweetened. Sweetend pastries are often describe as <em>Baker's Confectionery</em>
           The word "Pastries" suggests many kinds of baked products. pastries are made from ingredient such as; flour, butter, baking powder,eggs etc.
           we have different types of pastries:
           <li>Shortcrust pastry.</li> <li>Flaky Pastries.</li> <li>Puff Pastries.</li> <li>Beef Bun Pastries.</li>
           <li>Mince Pies Pastries.</li> <li>Croissant Pastries.</li> <li>Many More.</li>
           <h4>Subscribe to our Blog, so you can see different recipes for this different types of Pastries when we post them.</h4>
        </p>

          <h1><p><u>Food</u></p></h1>
          <p>Food substance consisting essentally of protein, carbonhydrate,
               fat and other nutrient used in the body of an organism to substain growth and vital processes and furnish energy. 
               food is usually of plant, animal or funigal origin and contains essential nutrient.
               in Nigeria, every wedding serves his guest with good food. most guest will expect to get fed when you invite them to celebrate your big day.
               Your wedding food selection will depend on the theme and style of your wedding as well as the time of day your wedding takes place.
               Here is the three most popular wedding food.
               <li><u>Appetiser:</u> is a tasting menu alternative to the sit down dinner. if you are planning a relatively short wedding reception and suit a cocktail party style.
                Appetiser typically works out a lot cheaper than a full meals examples are colourful sushi, miniature dessert,small chops etc. </li>

                <li>
                    <u> A wedding Buffet:</u>A buffet is typically more affordable option than sit down dinners. with a buffet you can serve a greaterr variety of food to suit different taste  
                    and guest able to eat as little as they want. A buffet is a less formal and more laid back choice for wedding food and is perfect for a relaxed reception such as garden wedding.
                
                </li>

                <li>
                    <u>Sit Down Dinner:</u> this is an elegant option. Your guest will be waited on and wont need to leave their tables and this is a good idea you have to reduced mobility.
                    A formal dinner is thought to be a more generous gesture towards your guest, especially those that have arrived from far away just to attend your wedding.
                    A ssit down dinner is a sophisticated choice just to impress your guest.
                </li>
                <h4>Subscribe to our Blog, so you can see different recipes for this different types of food when we post them.</h4>
            </p>
